---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const updated = 'June 2026';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — No Account, No Tracking | NestMath"
  description="How NestMath handles your data: calculations run in your browser, no account, no selling data. Privacy-friendly analytics only. Read the full policy."
  canonical="https://nestmath.app/privacy"
  schemaName="NestMath Privacy Policy"
  schemaDescription="How NestMath handles your data. Calculations run in your browser; no account required."
>
  <div class="relative overflow-hidden">
    <div
      class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[500px] h-[500px] rounded-full bg-primary-accent/20 blur-[120px] pointer-events-none -translate-y-1/4 translate-x-1/4"
      aria-hidden="true"
    ></div>

    <div class="max-w-[768px] mx-auto px-[24px] py-[64px]">
      <div class="mb-[48px]">
        <h1 class="text-headline-xl font-bold text-on-surface leading-tight -tracking-[0.02em] mb-[12px]">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="text-label-sm text-on-surface-variant">Last updated {updated}</p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-[40px]">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-headline-md font-semibold text-on-surface mb-[12px]">The short version</h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            Every calculation runs in your browser. The numbers you type into a calculator are never sent to a
            server, never stored by us, and never shared or sold. There are no accounts and no logins. You can
            use the entire site without giving up any personal information.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-headline-md font-semibold text-on-surface mb-[12px]">What stays on your device</h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            Some tools, like the Dashboard, let you save a snapshot of your results so they're there when you
            return. Those snapshots are written to your browser's local storage on your own device. They are
            not transmitted anywhere. You can delete them at any time with the "Clear all data" button on the
            Dashboard, or by clearing your browser's site data. On a shared or public computer, clear your data
            before you leave.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-headline-md font-semibold text-on-surface mb-[12px]">Analytics</h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            We use Vercel Web Analytics to understand which pages are visited and roughly how the site
            performs. It is privacy-friendly by design: it does not use cookies, does not build a profile of
            you, and does not track you across other websites. It collects aggregate, anonymized data such as
            page views, referring site, and general device type. It does not receive the values you enter into
            any calculator. You can read more in
            <a href="https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-primary hover:underline">Vercel's analytics privacy documentation</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-headline-md font-semibold text-on-surface mb-[12px]">Cookies</h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            NestMath does not set advertising or tracking cookies. Your theme preference and any saved
            snapshots are stored in local storage on your device, not in cookies sent to a server.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-headline-md font-semibold text-on-surface mb-[12px]">Third-party links</h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            The site links to outside services such as Ko-fi, GitHub, and LinkedIn. Once you follow a link to
            another site, that site's own privacy policy applies. We don't control how they handle your data.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-headline-md font-semibold text-on-surface mb-[12px]">Children</h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            NestMath is intended for a general adult audience and is not directed at children under 13. We do
            not knowingly collect personal information from anyone, including children.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-headline-md font-semibold text-on-surface mb-[12px]">Changes and contact</h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            We may update this policy as the site evolves. Material changes will be reflected in the "last
            updated" date above. The site is operated by ArcLayer LLC. For questions, reach out through
            <a href="https://github.com/paynekerz/NestMath" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-primary hover:underline">the GitHub repository</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
